		<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element  thegem-vc-text thegem-custom-6a55b9c67eb2f8907"  >
			<div class="wpb_wrapper">
				<p>The Kim Jaechul Graduate School of AI at Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology (&#8220;KAIST AI&#8221; for short) was established in Fall 2019 and is the first in Korea to offer MS, MS and PhD integrated, and PhD degrees in Artificial Intelligence. Our world-class faculty members (25 core, 42 affiliated and 8 Invited/Adjunct) are both brilliant scholars and committed teachers in the field of Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Data Mining, Computer Vision, Natural Language Processing, Robotics, Computer Systems Support for AI, and applied AI. They bring top-tier research experience as well as real-world problem-solving experience into the school based on their work experiences at the world’s leading research laboratories and tech companies including Google Brain, IBM T. J. Watson, Facebook AI Research, Disney Research, Microsoft Research, Nvidia Research, Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory, LinkedIn, Oracle, AT&amp;amp;T Bell Labs, Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology, Naver etc.</p>
<p>KAIST ranked 5th in the world (1st in Asia) in the total number of papers published in ICML, NeurIPS, and ICLR, the top machine learning conferences, over the past five years (2020-2024), following CMU, MIT, UC Berkeley, and Stanford University. (Source: <a href="https://csrankings.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://csrankings.org</a>).</p>
<p>In addition, KAIST ranked 5th in the world (4th in Asia) in the total number of papers published in ICML, NeurIPS, ICLR, ACL, EMNLP, NAACL, CVPR, ICCV, and ECCV, the top machine learning, natural language processing and computer vision conferences, over the past five years (2020-2024), following Peking University, CMU, Tsinghua University, and Shanghai Jiao Tong University. (Source: <a href="https://csrankings.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://csrankings.org</a>).</p>

